4.51
log
@Added Latin10 encoding.

This highlights a problem with our fonts - for Adobe compatibility, the
glyph /Tcommaaccent (formally known as /Tcedilla) needs to be modified to
actually have a comma below, rather than a cedilla. Adobe views U+0162 and
U+021A as being double-mappings of the same glyph.

